  "description": "WEAVE-V extended: Solomon's two-ring architecture with strandTune at +5.0 semitones (major third) instead of the documented fifth (7.02). Ring A sits at the fundamental; Ring B sits a major third above, coupled through the Solomon linking number. A single note produces an automatic major-third dyad where each pitch has its own internal phase coupling. The sound is wider and brighter than the Solomon fifth — a chord pad hiding inside a monophonic instrument.",
